{"ts":"2026-05-20T20:32:43.298Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-nbht"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm health output stays large even with --brief/--skip flags; add a true one-line summary mode"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Dogfood (2026-05-20): pm health emits ~1503 lines; --brief ~400 lines; --skip-integrity --skip-drift --skip-vectors ~1469 lines (skip flags cut compute time, not output size). For an agent that just needs ok:true/false plus failing-check names, this is heavy. The MCP pm_health brief projection helps but the CLI surface and brief size could shrink further. Proposal: a --summary mode returning just {ok, per-check name+status, warning_count} (a few lines), and ensure --skip-* also trims the corresponding output sections, not only the work."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","cli","dogfood","health","token-efficiency"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-05-20T20:32:43.298Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-05-20T20:32:43.298Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"A summary/one-line health mode returns ok + per-check status + warning_count in a few lines; --skip-* flags omit their sections from output; brief projection size measurably reduced; specs + 100% coverage green."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-rnpb"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"79ddd302ae0d23177d3a05a74b3c035826d80c2caa3f56b29e5f03c3e49ba32f","message":""}
